# CRM Rules

## Purpose
Inquiry pipeline per `docs/PRD.md` section 4.4 and `docs/BUSINESS_RULES.md` BR-C*.

## Requirements
- Default pipeline stages seeded per tenant on org create.
- Kanban API groups by stage_id; respect data scope by role.
- Duplicate phone warning within 30 days for open inquiries BR-C01.
- Closed Won requires property link or reason BR-C03.
- Closed Lost requires lost_reason BR-C04.
- Follow-ups: overdue escalation to manager after 48h BR-C06.
- Activities timeline append-only for audit types.

## Restrictions
- Sales executive cannot delete inquiries.
- Marketing role no CRM access.
- No stage skip without manager role or logged override.

## Best Practices
- Emit `inquiry.stage_changed` for notifications.
- Round-robin assignment configurable in org settings.
- Phone normalize to E.164 on write.

## Anti-Patterns
- Updating inquiry without activity log for stage changes.
- Global inquiry list without tenant filter.

## Examples

```typescript
await this.activityService.logStageChange(inquiry, fromStage, toStage, ctx.userId);
await this.eventEmitter.emit('inquiry.stage_changed', { inquiryId, tenantId });
```
